Bill put his eyes upon the sky.

It was a light indigo blue, with the dim sun lighting one side, and the gas giant Jool engulfing the other.

It was a pleasant sight. But, with his limited life support, he had no option other than grabbing some samples and planting his flag.

After he had planted his flag, Bill wondered; 'Will I come back someday to admire these skies again?'

With heavy hearts, bill hesitated on going into his capsule. And gazed into Jool.

It was bland. Seeing it again did not make it any significant, but bland.

He wondered why, and concluded that it had been gazed too deeply on the first time, and was depleted of all of its beauty.

So, Bill started heading towards his capsule. For his friends were waiting in orbit, and he had to tell them his experiences.
